13628.title: NASA Invites Media to Launch of New Mega-Moon Rocket and Spacecraft
13628.summary: NASA Invites Media to Launch of New Mega-Moon Rocket and Spacecraft

13629.title: La NASA invita a los medios al lanzamiento del nuevo mega-cohete y nave espacial lunares
13629.summary: Ya está abierta la acreditación de medios de comunicación para las actividades de pre-lanzamiento y lanzamiento relacionadas con la misión Artemis I de la NASA, la primera misión desde Apolo de sistemas de exploración construidos para llevar tripulación a bordo que viajará alrededor de la Luna.

13630.title: SpaceX stays busy with Starlink Group 4-6 launch
13630.summary: At 9:02 PM EST on January 18 (02:02 UTC on January 19), SpaceX launched another batch of 49 Starlink satellites to orbit aboard a flight-proven Falcon 9 rocket from Launch Complex 39A at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center (KSC). This launch time was an approximately 2-hour delay from the original target of 7:04 PM EST (00:02 UTC), which was forfeited in favor of the latter launch time prior to beginning the countdown.

13631.title: EarthDaily taps Loft Orbital to build and operate $150 million constellation
13631.summary: EarthDaily Analytics (EDA) said Jan. 18 it has selected condosat operator Loft Orbital to build, launch and operate a fleet of 10 Earth-observation satellites on its behalf.

13632.title: Raymond: Space Force in 2022 to focus on the design of a resilient architecture
13632.summary: The U.S. Space Force will turn more attention in the coming year to the design of the military’s future space architecture, chief of space operations Gen. John “Jay” Raymond said Jan. 18.

13633.title: SES absorbs SES Networks in streamlining effort
13633.summary: Satellite operator SES is absorbing its SES Networks business unit ahead of deploying its next-generation O3b mPOWER broadband constellation this year.

13634.title: Federal budget stalemate having ‘ripple effects’ on national security space missions
13634.summary: If a CR continues, two national security space missions funded in 2022 would have to be pushed into 2023 or beyond.

13640.title: SpaceX launches 2,000th Starlink satellite
13640.summary: A package of 49 Starlink satellites that rode a Falcon 9 rocket into orbit Tuesday night from Florida included the 2,000th spacecraft to launch into SpaceX’s broadband internet network.

13641.title: Satellogic raises $150 million from fund led by former treasury secretary
13641.summary: A fund led by Steven Mnuchin, former treasury secretary, will invest $150 million into Earth imaging company Satellogic, helping close a delayed merger with a special purpose acquisition corporation (SPAC).

13642.title: Cosmonauts begin Russian spacewalk to integrate new ISS module
13642.summary: Two Russian cosmonauts are conducting a spacewalk at the International Space Station (ISS) to fully configure and integrate the outpost’s newest module to support future operations.
